cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.IT 

This paper discusses a security issue in named data networking (NDN), which is a type of network architecture. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also proposes a detection scheme, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper involves designing a sketch data structure, which is related to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves analyzing and simulating the proposed scheme, which falls under the category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
